project.name: skylinkjs
project.description: SkylinkJS is an open-source client-side library for your web-browser that enables any website to easily leverage the capabilities of WebRTC and its direct data streaming powers between peers for audio/video conferencing or file transfer.

Skylink.name: Skylink
Skylink.description:
Before using Skylink

Please invoke {{#crossLink "Skylink/init:method"}}init(){{/crossLink}} method first to initialise the Application Key before using any functionalities in Skylink. If you do not have an Application Key, you may register for a Skylink platform developer account [to create one](http://developer.temasys.com.sg/register). To get started you may [visit the getting started page](https://temasys.github.io/how-to/2014/08/08/ Getting_started_with_WebRTC_and_SkylinkJS/), or alternatively fork a ready made demo application that uses Skylink Web SDK at [getaroom.io](http://getaroom.io/). For tips on using skylink and troubleshooting you can visit [our support portal](http://support.temasys.com.sg/support/solutions/folders/5000267498).

params.name: MESSAGING

DEFAULT | Value "messaging"
If init() method enableDataChannel option is enabled for both Peers, there is only one of this Datachannel type that can occur in the connection
The type where the Datachannel connection is primarily used for sending P2P messages.
This connection is persistent until the Peer connection of the Datachannel is closed, and can be used for data transfers when simultaneous transfers is not supported with the connecting Peer connection.

classitems.description: Contains the list of ICE connection states of a Peer connection.
classitems.name: ICE_CONNECTION_STATE

params.name: STARTING
params.description: Value "starting" The state when ICE agent is waiting for remote candidates supplied from ICE gathering from Peer.

params.name: CHECKING
params.description: Value "checking" The state when ICE agent has received the remote candidates from Peer and is checking for a usable candidate pair to start ICE connection.

params.name: CONNECTED
params.description:
Value "connected" The state when ICE agent has found a usable connection but still checking if there is a better candidate pair for better ICE connection.
At this stage, ICE connection is already established and may not necessarily go to COMPLETED.

params.name: COMPLETED
params.description:
Value "completed" The state when ICE agent has finished checking for the best candidate pairs for the best ICE connection.
At this stage, ICE connection is has been already established.

params.name: FAILED
params.description: Value "failed" The state when ICE agent had failed to find a ICE connection from all candidate pairs.

params.name: DISCONNECTED
params.description: Value "disconnected" The state when ICE agent connection is disconnected abruptly and may happen on a flaky network.

params.name: CLOSED
params.description: Value "closed" The state when ICE agent connection is closed and is no longer responding to any STUN requests.

params.name: TRICKLE_FAILED
params.description: Value "trickeFailed" The state when after ICE agent connection state had gone to FAILED and init() method enableIceTrickle option is enabled.

params.name: INTRODUCED
params.description: Value "introduced" The state when the SDK has introduced Peer (Sender) to Peer (Receiver) successfully.

params.name: ERROR
params.description: Value "error" The state when the SDK had failed to introduce Peer (Sender) to Peer (Receiver).

classitems.description: Contains the list of signaling states of a Peer connection.
classitems.name: PEER_CONNECTION_STATE

params.name: STABLE
params.description: Value "stable" The state when there is currently no OFFER or ANSWER exchanged.

params.name: HAVE_LOCAL_OFFER
params.description:
Value "have-local-offer" The state when there is a local OFFER sent to Peer.
After receiving remote ANSWER, the state will go to STABLE.

params.name: HAVE_REMOTE_OFFER
params.description:
Value "have-remote-offer" The state when there is a remote OFFER received from Peer.
After sending local ANSWER, the state will go to STABLE.

params.name: CLOSED
params.description: Value "closed" The state when signaling is closed and there is no OFFER or ANSWER exchanged anymore.

params.name: ERROR
params.description: Value "error" The state when setting local / remote OFFER or ANSWER fails and might cause a failure in establishing Peer connection.

classitems.description:
Note that for the next releases, the Keys and Values will change for a more descriptive term.
Contains the list of init() method SDK initialization errors.
classitems.name: READY_STATE_CHANGE_ERROR

params.name: API_INVALID
params.description: Value 4001 The error when provided Application Key is does not exists. Resolve this by finding if Application Key exists in your Skylink Developer Account.

params.name: API_DOMAIN_NOT_MATCH
params.description: Value 4002 The error when accessing backend IP address does not match Application Key configured domain. Resolve this by seeking support in Temasys Support Portal.

params.name: API_CORS_DOMAIN_NOT_MATCH
params.description: Value 4003 The error when accessing CORS domain does not match Application Key configured corsurl. Resolve this by configuring your Application Key CORS Url correctly in your Skylink Developer Account.

params.name: API_CREDENTIALS_INVALID
params.description: Value 4004 The error when credentials provided for Application Key is invalid. Resolve this by checking if credentials are generated correctly, or Secret used for generating credentials is correct. See init() method on how to generate the credentials.

params.name: API_CREDENTIALS_NOT_MATCH
params.description: Value 4005 The error when credentials provided for Application Key does not match provided duration and startDate in generated credentials. Resolve this by checking if credentials are generated correctly. See init() method on how to generate the credentials.

params.name: API_INVALID_PARENT_KEY
params.description: Value 4006 The error when provided Application Key has an invalid parent field value. Resolve this by providing another Application Key. You may check if it's valid by accessing your Skylink Developer Account and use any Application Keys from the displayed list of Application Keys.

params.name: API_NO_MEETING_RECORD_FOUND
params.description: Value 4010 The error when provided Persistent Room enabled key does not have any meeting records that matches the credentials provided in init() method. See Persistent Rooms and how it works.

params.name: NO_SOCKET_IO
params.description: Value 1 The error when there is no socket.io-client dependency loaded before the SDK. Resolve this by loading the dependency based on the correct versions following SkylinkJS release versions.

params.name: NO_XMLHTTPREQUEST_SUPPORT
params.description: Value 2 The error when there is no XMLHttpRequest API interface supported in the browser. Resolve this by switching to one of our supported browsers list.

params.name: NO_WEBRTC_SUPPORT
params.description: Value 3 The error when there is no RTCPeerConnection API interface supported in the browser, which the Temasys Plugin does not support and is not installed in the browser. Resolve this by switching to one of our supported browsers list, or if browser is Safari or IE in our supported browsers list, prompt users to install the Temasys Plugin.

params.name: NO_PATH
params.description: Value 4 The error when invalid init() method options are provided. Resolve this by ensuring correct init() method options are provided.

params.name: ADAPTER_NO_LOADED
params.description: Value 7 The error when there is no adapterjs dependency loaded before the SDK. Resolve this by loading the dependency based on the correct versions following SkylinkJS release versions.

params.name: XML_HTTP_REQUEST_ERROR
params.description: Value -1 The error when there is no response from server when requesting to start connection session. Resolve this by diagnosing network connections or refreshing the page. You may report this to Temasys Support Portal if both solutions does not work.

classitems.description: Contains the list of init() method SDK initialization errors current HTTP request status.

params.name: NO_REQUEST_MADE

params.name: REQUEST_FAILED

classitems.name: SOCKET_FALLBACK

params.name: NON_FALLBACK
params.description:
Value "nonfallback"
This has been deprecated and will be eventually be removed or changed into other seperate states in next releases.
The state when socket is attempting to reconnect the first port and transports used that had failed.
Protocol: http:, https:
Transports: WebSocket, Polling

params.name: FALLBACK_PORT
params.description:
Value "fallbackPortNonSSL" The state when socket is attempting to reconnect the next available fallback port.
Protocol: http:
Transports: WebSocket

params.name: FALLBACK_PORT_SSL
params.description:
Value "fallbackPortSSL" The state when socket is attempting to reconnect the next available fallback port.
Protocol: https:
Transports: WebSocket

params.name: LONG_POLLING
params.description:
Value "fallbackLongPollingNonSSL" The state when socket switches to Polling transports from WebSocket transports for a better attempt at reconnectivity after all reconnection attempts with all available ports has failed.
The socket will start the reconnect attempt with next fallback port starting from the first port used.
This state may occur directly after NON_FALLBACK if WebSocket transports is not supported.
Protocol: http:
Transports: Polling

params.name: LONG_POLLING_SSL
params.description:
Value "fallbackLongPollingSSL" The state when socket switches to Polling transports from WebSocket transports for a better attempt at reconnectivity after all reconnection attempts with all available ports has failed.
The socket will start the reconnect attempt with next fallback port starting from the first port used.
This state may occur directly after NON_FALLBACK if WebSocket transports is not supported.
Protocol: https:
Transports: Polling

classitems.description:
Note that configuring these options might not necessarily result in the desired type (TCP/UDP) of connection as it is depends on how the browser connects the connection.
Contains the list of available TURN transports configuration options to pass when constructing a connection object.
classitems.name: TURN_TRANSPORT

params.name: TCP
params.description:
Value "tcp" The option to connect with setting only TCP transports. EXAMPLE TURN URLS OUTPUT
turn:turnurl:123?transport=tcp
turn:turnurl?transport=tcp
turn:turnurl:1234?transport=tcp

params.name: UDP
params.description:
Value "udp" The option to connect with setting only UDP transports. EXAMPLE TURN URLS OUTPUT
turn:turnurl:123?transport=udp
turn:turnurl?transport=udp
turn:turnurl:1234?transport=udp

params.name: ANY
params.description:
DEFAULT | Value "any" The option to connect with any transports that is configured by the Skylink Platform. EXAMPLE TURN URLS OUTPUT
turn:turnurl:123?transport=tcp
turn:turnurl?transport=udp
turn:turnurl:1234
turn:turnurl

params.name: NONE
params.description:
Value "none" The option to connect without setting any transports. EXAMPLE TURN URLS OUTPUT
turn:turnurl:123
turn:turnurl
turn:turnurl:1234

params.name: ALL
params.description:
Value "all" The option to connect with setting both TCP and UDP transports. EXAMPLE TURN URLS OUTPUT
turn:turnurl:123?transport=tcp
turn:turnurl:123?transport=udp
turn:turnurl?transport=tcp
turn:turnurl?transport=udp
turn:turnurl:1234?transport=tcp
turn:turnurl:1234?transport=udp

classitems.description: Event triggered when room connection information is being retrieved from platform server. - This is also triggered when init() is invoked, but the socket connection events like channelOpen does not get triggered but stops at readyStateChange event.
classitems.name: readyStateChange

params.name: readyState
params.description:
The current ready state of the retrieval when the event is triggered.
  [Rel: Skylink.READY_STATE_CHANGE]

params.name: error
params.description: The error object thrown when there is a failure in retrieval. If received as null, it means that there is no errors.

props.name: status
props.description:
Http status when retrieving information.
  May be empty for other errors.

props.name: errorCode
props.description: The READY_STATE_CHANGE_ERROR if there is an readyStateChange event error that caused the failure for initialising Skylink. [Rel: Skylink.READY_STATE_CHANGE_ERROR]

props.name: content
props.description:
The exception thrown that caused the failure
  for initialising Skylink.

props.name: status
props.description:
The XMLHttpRequest status code received
  when exception is thrown that caused the failure for initialising Skylink.

params.name: room
params.description:
The selected room connection information that Skylink is attempting
  to retrieve the information for to start connection to.

classitems.description:
Note that this method is required to call before using any other functionalities except Event methods like on() method, off() method or once() method. By default, the SDK uses CORS authentication. To use credentials based authentication, configure the credentials parameter.
Method that initializes the Skylink object to start connection session.
classitems.name: init

params.name: options
params.description:
The parameter for configuration settings.
Providing this value as a "String" reads as appKey.

props.name: appKey
props.description: The parameter to configure the Application Key.

props.name: defaultRoom
props.description:
This fallbacks to the value of Application Key configured if not provided.
The parameter to configure the default Room name that the SDK uses when no room parameter is provided in joinRoom() method.

props.name: roomServer
props.description:
This is for SDK debugging purposes and it is NOT RECOMMENDED to modify the value. To use this, have to provide the Protocol Relative URL value ("//") before the domain name. Ensure that no ("/") value is provided at the end of the value.
The parameter to configure the API server to start connection session.

props.name: region
props.description:
This has been deprecated and it is not recommended to configure this value anymore.
The parameter to configure the nearest regional server for the SDK to connect to. [Rel: Skylink.attr.REGIONAL_SERVER]

props.name: enableIceTrickle
props.description:
Note that setting this to false may result in a slower connection.
The parameter to enable trickle ICE connections for faster connectivity. See: What is ICE and how it works

props.name: enableDataChannel
props.description:
Note that setting this to false will disable sendBlobData() method, sendURLData() method and sendP2PMessage() method functionalities. You will not be able to receive any P2P messages as well. Additionally, even with this enabled, if there is a connecting Peer that does not have enableDataChannel enabled, the following above functionalities will not work with that particular Peer connection.
The parameter to enable Datachannel connections.

props.name: enableTURNServer
props.description:
Note that this only filters the ICE servers when starting Peer connection. To enforce TURN connections, configure forceTURN parameter instead.
The parameter to enable using TURN ICE servers when starting a Peer connection.
Disabling this will filter out all TURN ICE servers passed in Peer connections.

props.name: enableSTUNServer
props.description:
The parameter to enable using STUN ICE servers when starting a Peer connection.
Disabling this will filter out all STUN ICE servers passed in Peer connections.

props.name: forceTURN
props.description:
Note that if TURN is not enabled for the Application Key configured, Peer connections will not be able to connect.
The parameter to enforce TURN ICE connections.
Enabling this will filter out all STUN ICE servers as well.

props.name: usePublicSTUN
props.description:
The parameter to enable using publicly available STUN ICE servers when starting a Peer connection.
Disabling this will filter out all publicly available STUN ICE servers.

props.name: TURNServerTransport
props.description:
The parameter to
  configure the TURN ICE servers transports.
  [Rel: Skylink.attr.TURN_TRANSPORT]

props.name: credentials
props.description:
Note that you require the configure the correct startDateTime and duration used when generating the credentials to configure the SDK to use credentials based authentication, By default, when credentials is not provided, the SDK will use CORS based authentication. Additionally, take note that using credentials based authentication does not allow you to join the Room based on the room paramter provided in joinRoom() method.
The parameter to use credentials based authentication to start connection session. See: Authenticating SDK connection sessions.

props.name: startDateTime
props.description: The parameter to configure the credentials starting DateTime. This value has to be set in (ISO 8601 format), which can be retrieved from the Date object Date.getISOString() method.

props.name: duration
props.description:
The parameter to configure the credentials connection session duration in Hours. EXAMPLES:
30 mins: 0.5
1 hour, 24mins: 1.4
2 hours, 30mins: 2.5

props.name: credentials
props.description:
The parameter to configure the credentials connection session authentication string.
This requires you to generate with your configured Application Key Secret, provided credentials - startDateTime, duration and defaultRoom values. INSTRUCTIONS ON GENERATING CREDENTIALS STRING:
  1. Concatenate the defaultRoom, credentials - duration and startDateTime. var concatStr = defaultRoom + "_" + duration + "_" + startDateTimeStamp;
  2. Hash the concatStr value with the Application Key Secret using SHA-1 In this example, we use the CryptoJS.HmacSHA1 function . var hash = CryptoJS.HmacSHA1(concatStr, secret);
  3. Convert the hash to a Base64 encoded string. In this example, we use the CryptoJS.enc.Base64 function. var base64String = hash.toString(CryptoJS.enc.Base64);
  4. Encode the Base64 encoded string to a URI component using UTF-8 encoding with encodeURIComponent() function. var credentialsStr = encodeURIComponent(base64String);

props.name: audioFallback
props.description: The parameter to configure to retrieve audio only as a fallback when retrieving audio and video fails in getUserMedia() method.

props.name: forceSSL
props.description:
By default, if user is accessing the SDK from https: protocol, SSL connections are already enabled.
The parameter to enforce SSL connections when starting connection session and Room socket connection.

props.name: audioCodec
props.description:
The parameter to configure
  the audio codec for audio streams.
  [Rel: Skylink.attr.AUDIO_CODEC]

props.name: videoCodec
props.description:
The parameter to configure
  the audio codec for video streams.
  [Rel: Skylink.attr.VIDEO_CODEC]

props.name: socketTimeout
props.description: The parameter to configure the timeout to wait when there is no connection response before triggering as CONNECTION_FAILED or RECONNECTION_FAILED. [Rel: Skylink.attr.SOCKET_ERROR]

props.name: forceTURNSSL
props.description:
By default, if user is accessing the SDK from https: protocol, TURN SSL connections are already enabled. Note that if the browser does not support the turns: protocol, SSL ports will be used instead.
The parameter to enforce SSL connections for TURN ICE server connections.

params.name: callbackFn
